#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
apply_v332.py — regime demotion policy + EOD trade-style fix + EOD/pusher probe
================================================================================
Three items from the 2026-06-12 operator session:

1. EOD "CLOSES EVERYTHING" ROOT CAUSE FOUND — the v19.34.301/302
   naked-flatten guard (runs 15:45-16:00 ET) still read the raw
   per-trade `close_at_eod` ATTRIBUTE, which v19.34.245 had already
   declared broken (blanket default-True fallback) when it fixed the
   MAIN EOD pass to resolve from the trade-style POLICY. Result: swing/
   position holds whose attribute was stale-True were treated as
   intraday and FORCE-FLATTENED by the 15:56 v302 sweep — "EOD closes
   every position regardless of trade style". The guard now calls
   `should_close_at_eod(trade)` exactly like the main pass.

2. REGIME DEMOTION POLICY (operator-approved design):
   • new entries: `bot._current_regime` is now kept LIVE — it was
     frozen at "RISK_ON" since boot (`_update_market_regime` was never
     wired into any loop), so the sizing multiplier table NEVER engaged.
     Now new entries size for the regime we're actually in.
   • existing positions: an adverse flip must PERSIST 20 min
     (REGIME_DEMOTION_CONFIRM_MIN) before demotion; a revert cancels it
     (whipsaw guard — no spread paid on VIX blips).
   • demotion is SOFTWARE-STOP ONLY → ZERO IB order surgery → ZERO new
     orphan-order surface (operator's explicit concern). Profitable
     ≥0.25R → stop-to-BE via the proven StopManager path; otherwise the
     internal stop ratchets halfway to entry (never looser, never so
     close it triggers instantly). M0 ladder legs absorb the new stop
     in-place on the next manage tick; classic brackets keep their IB
     hard stop as the disaster backstop.
   • scope: intraday + swing styles. Scalps ride their HSBG brackets;
     multi_day/position/investment theses ignore intraday flips.
   • RISK_OFF / CONFIRMED_DOWN confirmed → demote longs;
     RISK_ON confirmed after a risk-off state → demote shorts;
     CAUTION → sizing only.

3. EOD/PUSHER EVIDENCE PROBE — ships scripts/diag_eod_pusher.py
   (read-only) that mines the DB for: close reason × trade-style audit
   15:30-16:10 ET (proves what each EOD path flattened), per-minute
   pusher ingest timeline (shows WHEN data dies vs the 15:45 cutoffs),
   state_integrity_events, EOD heartbeats, queue completion gaps.
   NOTE: the 15:45 "pusher death" window exactly matches the bot's
   RegT machinery (15:45 hard entry cut + EOD close pass + naked-guard
   polling). Run the probe after Monday's close for the verdict.

Also updates test_eod_force_flatten_bracketed_v302.py fakes to the
policy contract and ships tests/test_v332_regime_demotion.py (12 tests).

SAFE TO RUN MULTIPLE TIMES (idempotent). No DB phase.
Run from repo root:   .venv/bin/python /tmp/apply_v332.py
Then: git add -A && git commit -m "v332: regime demotion + EOD style fix" && git push
Then restart the backend.
"""
